'''''Mylothris citrina''''' is a [[butterfly]] in the [[Pieridae]] family. It is found in [[Uganda]], the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]] and [[Tanzania]].<ref name=ATBUT>[http://atbutterflies.com/downloads/pieridae_anthocharidini.doc Afrotropical Butterflies: File D <U+2013> Pierini - Tribe Aporiina]</ref> The habitat consists of forests.

==Subspecies==
*''Mylothris citrina citrina'' (north-eastern Tanzania)
*''Mylothris citrina holochroma'' <small>Talbot, 1944</small> (Democratic Republic of Congo)
*''Mylothris citrina orientalis'' <small>Talbot, 1946</small> (Uganda)

